- `abs(sin(v * 6π - 1.57))` — 1.57 = π/2. This is `abs(sin(v*6π - π/2))` = `abs(-cos(v*6π))` = `abs(cos(v*6π))`. This peaks at v = 0, 1/6, 2/6, 3/6, 4/6, 5/6, 1 (where cos = ±1). At these points, haustraPouch = +0.3 (outward). 

So the pattern is:
- At v = 0: pouch (+0.3)
- At v = 1/12: fold (-0.65)
- At v = 2/12 (1/6): pouch (+0.3)
- At v = 3/12 (1/4): fold (-0.65)
- At v = 4/12 (1/3): pouch (+0.3)
