`fract(0.08t + 1.5v)`: for a fixed phase value f, v = (f - 0.08t)/1.5. As t increases, v decreases. So the wave moves backward (-v), toward the camera. That's the wrong direction.

`fract(0.08t - 1.5v)`: v = (0.08t - f)/1.5. As t increases, v increases. Wave moves forward (+v). ✓

