## Assistant (Build · Big Pickle · 5.6s)

Done. Press F3 to open the debug panel — you'll see a **Tunnel Controls** window with six sliders:

| Slider | What it does | Range |
|---|---|---|
| **Motion Amount** | Amplitude of peristaltic waves and breathing — crank it for wild writhing | 0–3 |
| **Roundness** | Strength of the triangular cross-section — 0 = perfect circle, higher = more lobed | 0–0.6 |
| **Haustra Strength** | How deep the haustral constriction rings pinch inward — 0 removes them entirely | 0–2 |
| **Animation Speed** | Global multiplier on all `time` inputs in the shader — speed up/slow down the whole蠕动 | 0–5 |
| **Camera Speed** | How fast you fly through the tunnel | 0–5 |
| **Curvature Strength** | Amplitude of the path wobble in `GrowPath` — 0 = dead straight, higher = more serpentine | 0–5 |

`curvatureStrength` affects newly generated path segments live, so you'll see curves change as the tunnel grows ahead of you.

