Actually, for GLSL 330 core, I can use this approach. Let me design the shader:

```glsl
// More organic haustra - random spacing and depth
float haustraPos = v * 5.0; // base frequency
float randOffset = sin(v * 1.3247 + v * v * 0.001) * 0.5 + 0.5; // pseudo-random variation
float haustraFreq = 4.0 + randOffset * 3.0; // varies between 4-7 per V-unit
float hfPos = fract(v * haustraFreq + sin(v * 0.7) * 0.2);
float hfDist = min(hfPos, 1.0 - hfPos) * 2.0;
float haustraDepth = 0.4 + randOffset * 0.6; // varies depth
float haustra = -pow(1.0 - hfDist, 2.0) * haustraStrength * haustraDepth;
```

