Build succeeded. Let me summarize.

Done. New shader effects, all driven by a `hash` function for organic randomness:

**Random haustra:** spacing varies from 3.5–7 per V-unit (was fixed at 5) with a small phase jitter, depth varies 0.3–1.0× slider. No two constrictions are alike.

**Random bulges:** at random positions along the tube (`floor(v×2.5)` hashed), a bulge swells on one side (`cos(angle×2 + randomPhase)`) and slowly shifts over time. Looks like gas pockets pushing the wall outward.

**Gurgle:** three fast, narrow `pow(sin, 10)` pulses at different frequencies (7, 5.3, 6.7) and phases — quick localized bubbles that pop along the tunnel. Random spacing because the frequencies are irrational ratios.

**Back-and-forth peristalsis:** two opposing waves — `forwardWave` (t×0.2 − v×2π, moving away) and `backwardWave` (t×0.12 + v×2.5, moving toward camera) — plus a very slow `slowBreath` (t×0.05). The tunnel contracts and expands in both directions simultaneously, creating chaotic, churning motion.

